1
00:00:31,517 --> 00:00:34,944
=Love Actually S5=

2
00:00:35,648 --> 00:00:36,919
(All the girls have invited someone.)

3
00:00:36,919 --> 00:00:39,080
Xuan.

4
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,040
Hi.

5
00:00:40,599 --> 00:00:41,520
Who did you invite?

6
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:42,959
I need to talk to you.

7
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:44,919
It's okay.

8
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:48,720
I invited Zhou Youling and Lu Bingkun.

9
00:00:49,159 --> 00:00:49,880
What's so funny?

10
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:50,520
I see.

11
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:51,520
You invited him after I did.

12
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:53,200
I invited Zhou Youling too.

13
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,639
He's so busy today.

14
00:00:54,639 --> 00:00:55,919
Did you only invite him?

15
00:00:55,919 --> 00:00:56,680
Yeah.

16
00:01:01,720 --> 00:01:02,639
It's okay.

17
00:01:06,796 --> 00:01:08,640
(Drop)

18
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:09,959
Are you okay?

19
00:01:09,959 --> 00:01:10,720
Let me.

20
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:12,519
I made a mistake.

21
00:01:12,519 --> 00:01:13,400
It's okay.

22
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:13,800
Don't worry.

23
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:14,519
We can wash this again later.

24
00:01:14,519 --> 00:01:15,879
Is your outfit okay?

25
00:01:15,879 --> 00:01:16,400
I...

26
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:17,279
It's okay.

27
00:01:17,279 --> 00:01:18,239
Luckily it's white.

28
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:19,959
There's rice cake.

29
00:01:19,959 --> 00:01:21,720
I bought it. Do you want some?

30
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:22,279
I'll have a little.

31
00:01:22,279 --> 00:01:22,959
If you want some, I'll cook it.

32
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:24,839
Stir-fried rice cake.

33
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,440
Such a virtuous woman.

34
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:31,239
Great composition.

35
00:01:32,519 --> 00:01:33,160
Looks nice.

36
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:34,959
Today's female chef.

37
00:01:35,879 --> 00:01:36,440
It's a bit spicy.

38
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:38,480
I hope you can handle it.

39
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:38,919
Smells amazing.

40
00:01:38,919 --> 00:01:39,360
Okay.

41
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,199
Thanks.

42
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:46,360
Come and eat, baby.

43
00:01:53,599 --> 00:01:54,040
Amazing!

44
00:01:57,239 --> 00:01:58,040
Liu.

45
00:01:58,959 --> 00:01:59,639
Come on, baby.

46
00:02:00,239 --> 00:02:01,559
If you don't have any symptoms,

47
00:02:01,559 --> 00:02:02,599
just take one as prevention.

48
00:02:02,599 --> 00:02:03,319
(Giving Liu medicine before the date)
If you have symptoms

49
00:02:03,319 --> 00:02:04,040
like a sore throat,

50
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,000
or if it gets a bit serious,

51
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,559
take all three.

52
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,320
I'm off, ladies.

53
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,520
Good luck on your date.

54
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,279
Good luck!

55
00:02:10,279 --> 00:02:11,279
Have fun.

56
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:16,000
I didn't see the guys come down.

57
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,080
I was just thinking

58
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:18,559
that maybe we should just

59
00:02:18,559 --> 00:02:20,360
have Zhou Youling sit here.

60
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,919
(Invitee: Zhou Youling)

61
00:02:21,919 --> 00:02:23,600
Don't need to go out.

62
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,720
Let's just hang out here.

63
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,440
You invited

64
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,199
Zhou Youling?

65
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:28,279
Zhou Youling and BK.

66
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:34,000
He'll probably be too exhausted today.

67
00:02:35,679 --> 00:02:37,559
Do you have one date or two?

68
00:02:37,559 --> 00:02:38,600
I have two.

69
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:39,399
Who's your other date?

70
00:02:39,399 --> 00:02:40,119
Same as you.

71
00:02:40,119 --> 00:02:40,800
BK.

72
00:02:41,679 --> 00:02:43,279
Then BK must be pretty tired too.

73
00:02:43,279 --> 00:02:44,119
We could meet him together.

74
00:02:44,119 --> 00:02:45,600
Let's all go together.

75
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:52,479
You are really graceful.

76
00:02:52,479 --> 00:02:53,720
Both you and your horse are so graceful.

77
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,600
(Graceful Mr. Zhou
and the graceful horse)

78
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,080
(Wild little pony)
I think my horse is quite wild.

79
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:57,399
I have to keep pulling on the reins.

80
00:02:57,399 --> 00:02:59,119
(Looking back)
It's feistier than the last time I rode.

81
00:02:59,119 --> 00:02:59,679
That one

82
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,080
(Looking back)
won't pick up speed

83
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,320
no matter how hard I try.

84
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:03,720
(Looking back)
But this one will just fly away

85
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:04,559
if you don't tie it up.

86
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,119
Hold on, I can't hear you very well.

87
00:03:07,119 --> 00:03:07,639
I need to speed up.

88
00:03:07,639 --> 00:03:07,880
(Out of service area)

89
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:08,279
Giddy up.

90
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:09,880
Move faster.

91
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,279
Can you come next to me?

92
00:03:12,279 --> 00:03:13,160
I want to.

93
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,039
My neck's getting tired
looking back at you.

94
00:03:15,039 --> 00:03:15,679
Go.

95
00:03:17,222 --> 00:03:20,440
(Stop)

96
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,479
Go.

97
00:03:21,479 --> 00:03:22,960
(Stop, stop too)
Look, when yours stops, it stops too.

98
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,639
(Not moving at all)
Take a couple more steps forward. Go.

99
00:03:24,639 --> 00:03:25,000
Go.

100
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:27,279
Go, baby.

101
00:03:27,279 --> 00:03:28,639
(Instantly follows)
It just follows along.

102
00:03:29,279 --> 00:03:30,759
And it doesn't even walk as fast
as yours.

103
00:03:30,759 --> 00:03:31,720
It's so obedient.

104
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:34,639
So do you usually stay in Shanghai?

105
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,039
Yes, I've always been in Shanghai.

106
00:03:37,039 --> 00:03:37,759
You're Shanghainese?

107
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:38,279
Yeah, I'm Shanghainese.

108
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:39,880
Where are you from?

109
00:03:40,399 --> 00:03:41,360
I'm from Harbin.

110
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,960
But my mom is from Shenyang.

111
00:03:45,279 --> 00:03:46,720
Then you have some Northeast genes.

112
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:47,520
No wonder you're so tall.

113
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,600
I have Northeast blood.

114
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:50,320
Yesterday, Zhuoran said

115
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:52,240
the three of us are "Hei-Ji-Liao".

116
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:52,880
(From Jilin, From Liaoning,
From Heilongjiang)

117
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:53,360
Right.

118
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,119
We are riding very elegantly.

119
00:03:57,679 --> 00:03:58,679
Why are you always following it?

120
00:03:58,679 --> 00:04:00,240
Can't you overtake it?

121
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,399
Can you take the lead?

122
00:04:01,399 --> 00:04:03,440
(Horse: Won't listen, won't listen)

123
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,440
Why do I feel like this horse

124
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,520
doesn't like me?

125
00:04:06,199 --> 00:04:07,080
(Chen Jianying's horse from last time)
It likes you.

126
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:09,199
Sometimes I kick it,
but it still doesn't move.

127
00:04:09,759 --> 00:04:10,479
Kick it, harder.

128
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,679
I'm afraid I'll hurt it.

129
00:04:12,679 --> 00:04:13,360
You won't.

130
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,920
You should say "go".

131
00:04:20,975 --> 00:04:21,279
(Go)

132
00:04:21,279 --> 00:04:22,119
Go.

133
00:04:23,279 --> 00:04:24,119
Giddy up.

134
00:04:27,073 --> 00:04:27,839
(The coach comes to help)

135
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:28,839
A little harder.

136
00:04:28,839 --> 00:04:29,399
Harder?

137
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:29,679
Yes.

138
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:31,880
I'm already using a lot of force.

139
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:33,600
(Immediately pulling away)
Giddy up.

140
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,519
Giddy up.

141
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:34,959
Giddy up.

142
00:04:34,959 --> 00:04:36,239
Wait for me.

143
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:37,839
You're pretty fast.

144
00:04:38,399 --> 00:04:39,160
No.

145
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,079
Halt.

146
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,640
Moon really listens to you.

147
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:45,696
(The horse-taming man)

148
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:47,720
Giddy up.

149
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:48,480
We're side by side.

150
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,160
That's great.

151
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:51,519
Okay, they have their own rhythm.

152
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:55,440
They need to feel it.

153
00:04:55,839 --> 00:04:57,279
Yeah, they need to take it slow
and feel it.

154
00:04:57,279 --> 00:04:58,079
Right, we need to feel them.

155
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:00,480
They can't be rushed.

156
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,000
I feel like

157
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,920
the horse needs to feel each person too.

158
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,079
I think so too.

159
00:05:07,239 --> 00:05:08,760
Look, I think now

160
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:09,799
it can probably feel me.

161
00:05:09,799 --> 00:05:11,720
When I pull it, it'll slow down.

162
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,040
Indeed.

163
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:18,600
Time to eat.

164
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:19,959
It's hungry.

165
00:05:19,959 --> 00:05:20,720
It's time to eat, baby.

166
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:24,320
Do you know how horses sleep?

167
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,600
Don't horses sleep?

168
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,239
How could horses not need to sleep?

169
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,640
Then how do they sleep?

170
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:29,920
Normally they sleep standing up.

171
00:05:30,559 --> 00:05:31,920
But it seems like they also

172
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,760
sometimes lie down.

173
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,079
There's also a saying that

174
00:05:36,079 --> 00:05:38,119
if a horse likes to lie down
for a really long time,

175
00:05:38,119 --> 00:05:39,519
it means

176
00:05:39,519 --> 00:05:41,799
it's about to die.

177
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:42,279
Yeah.

178
00:05:42,279 --> 00:05:44,079
A fine horse

179
00:05:44,079 --> 00:05:44,760
that never kneels.

180
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,359
Giddy up.

181
00:05:50,959 --> 00:05:52,519
Then let's just

182
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:53,959
apply the colors of our design.

183
00:05:53,959 --> 00:05:54,839
You can draw the second one.

184
00:05:54,839 --> 00:05:55,320
Okay.

185
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:55,720
Come on.

186
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,720
You can even compliment that?

187
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,079
Full of emotional value.

188
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:05,519
I can't come up with a compliment.

189
00:06:05,519 --> 00:06:06,320
I just went "hmm".

190
00:06:08,239 --> 00:06:08,880
Okay.

191
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,279
So after you graduated,

192
00:06:15,279 --> 00:06:16,320
you started working in this industry?

193
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:17,079
Yes.

194
00:06:17,079 --> 00:06:18,640
You've been very determined

195
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:20,519
in choosing this career?

196
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,239
Rather than saying I'm determined,

197
00:06:24,239 --> 00:06:26,119
it's more like I'm just not...

198
00:06:26,119 --> 00:06:27,160
Not interested in other things.

199
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,559
Yeah, but actually,

200
00:06:28,559 --> 00:06:30,239
when we first started, I used AI

201
00:06:30,239 --> 00:06:31,320
to do the company website

202
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:33,040
and the hangtag design.

203
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,839
I've also done

204
00:06:36,839 --> 00:06:37,959
graphic design work.

205
00:06:37,959 --> 00:06:39,760
I can do anything to build the brand.

206
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,200
Excellent.

207
00:06:41,679 --> 00:06:42,559
So do I

208
00:06:43,959 --> 00:06:44,959
need to fill in the color?

209
00:06:44,959 --> 00:06:46,239
What do you think?

210
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,279
You can try this.

211
00:06:49,279 --> 00:06:52,119
For example, here you could use
a deeper red,

212
00:06:52,119 --> 00:06:53,880
and then gradually blend
into some orange

213
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:54,440
or pink.

214
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,720
Then add some more red.

215
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,760
Then I'll fill in the fish tail first.

216
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:58,320
Okay.

217
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,440
A deep red for the fish tail.

218
00:07:01,839 --> 00:07:03,079
Sometimes when drawing

219
00:07:03,079 --> 00:07:04,279
or doing these things,

220
00:07:04,279 --> 00:07:05,839
it can help you achieve

221
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:08,279
a flow state that you can't during work.

222
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:09,959
What state?

223
00:07:09,959 --> 00:07:10,559
A flow state.

224
00:07:11,079 --> 00:07:11,760
A flow state.

225
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,600
You'll be immersed.

226
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,920
Your mind is very calm,

227
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:18,200
and you'll feel a subtle sense of joy.

228
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:18,959
That's flow state.

229
00:07:19,239 --> 00:07:20,000
Hiding one's light under a bushel.

230
00:07:20,519 --> 00:07:21,200
Is that accurate?

231
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,328
(Uh oh, wrong expression)

232
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,640
Not exactly.

233
00:07:27,559 --> 00:07:28,200
Nurturing the mind.

234
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,559
You could put it that way.

235
00:07:30,399 --> 00:07:31,720
Transition a bit more towards the front.

236
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,664
(Better just draw!)

237
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:37,679
I can add a bit of white
to balance it out.

238
00:07:37,679 --> 00:07:38,279
Okay.

239
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:40,760
Do you prefer cool tones,

240
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,799
or just contrasting colors?

241
00:07:42,799 --> 00:07:43,359
Contrasting colors.

242
00:07:43,839 --> 00:07:45,119
But I think for fireworks,

243
00:07:45,559 --> 00:07:46,320
you don't need cool tones.

244
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,440
They should just be brilliant.

245
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,679
So do you hope your love

246
00:07:49,679 --> 00:07:50,799
is like fireworks,

247
00:07:50,799 --> 00:07:52,679
brilliant and dazzling?

248
00:07:52,679 --> 00:07:54,799
Or do you prefer...

249
00:07:54,799 --> 00:07:55,600
A steady, enduring love?

250
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,279
Steady and enduring.

251
00:07:56,279 --> 00:07:57,160
More stable.

252
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,279
I'm quite conflicted on this.

253
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,559
I don't think I've ever experienced

254
00:08:03,559 --> 00:08:06,040
really passionate,
earth-shattering love.

255
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:08,839
Or a grand kind of love.

256
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,640
But I really hope that my date and I

257
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:14,000
(Prefer "brilliant" love)
can always be in passionate love.

258
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,399
I don't want a situation

259
00:08:15,399 --> 00:08:17,079
where our state is mismatched,

260
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:18,880
like when I might be in a lull,

261
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:19,480
but he isn't,

262
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:21,200
or when he's in a lull, but I don't.

263
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,119
I would hope

264
00:08:22,119 --> 00:08:23,920
the two of us are always
in passionate love.

265
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,440
It feels very idealistic.

266
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:27,119
Actually we're about the same, yeah.

267
00:08:30,559 --> 00:08:32,080
(Likes 'brilliant' love)
Yeah, we're both like that.

268
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:37,919
So what do you hope your partner

269
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:39,640
is like in life?

270
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,719
For instance, do you need him

271
00:08:43,239 --> 00:08:44,599
to give you little surprises every day,

272
00:08:44,599 --> 00:08:46,359
or would you rather

273
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:48,960
you two walk side by side?

274
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:49,960
I'd choose the latter.

275
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,119
(Walking side by side)

276
00:08:51,119 --> 00:08:52,200
I would prefer

277
00:08:53,039 --> 00:08:54,000
we have things to talk about,

278
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,000
and

279
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,919
we are able

280
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,840
to be mutually...

281
00:08:58,840 --> 00:08:59,479
Needed.

282
00:08:59,479 --> 00:09:00,960
Yeah, need and comfort each other.

283
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:01,719
And,

284
00:09:01,719 --> 00:09:02,679
as for little surprises,

285
00:09:02,679 --> 00:09:04,719
I think they are definitely
a spice of life.

286
00:09:04,719 --> 00:09:05,919
And I'm the kind of person...

287
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,960
If I prepare a little thoughtful thing,

